column5: Hey all.  Just introducing myself (apparently I better do that before posting!  :0)  Anyway, been fishign for a few years, mostly bass, pike and some panfishing when my freezer has some room!  I'm in the Niagara area, so most of my fishing is done at the Grand R., Niagara R., Fifty Point (rainbows...mmm), and some local conservation areas.  Thinking of joining a local bassmasters chapter...either Niagara, St. Catharines or Dunnville.  We'll see.  Anyway, happy fishing all!  Mike
Welcome aboard! Shore fisherman or boat or both?

Shore only.  I haven't the room for a boat right now.  My garage is filled with a 98 cavalier.  Oh yeah, I'm living the sweet life.  Hey, anyone in the market for a used car?  hahaha...  Forgot to mention Port Dalhousie too...not too bad for the trout, but not much luck this winter.
Welcome to the board and thanks for the Intro... many forget how important that really is
Welcome Mike,  Nice intro , look forward to your posts!  Cheers,  Jen
i am heading to port D later on today, just have to do my brakes on my car then i have all kinds of fish time...
fished port a bunch of times this winter and early spring for the bows but was pretty much empty-handed.  oh well.... thanks all.
may bump into you if you head by the whirlpool during the summer/fall, see you out on the water
